#1401
Inside the Gates~
  Inside the mighty gates the town looks quite drab.  The huts of the
commoners are made from the same hodgepodge of metal that the city
wall is.  In the center of town there is a small oasis that has been
formed in the dunes.  The center of the town is at a much lower
elevation than the outside ring of town making it possible to see
the entire town.  On the southern end of town a large tower is built
starting at the pool and rising towards the sky.  To the East and
West are small side streets that follow along with the walls.  A
sturdy looking ladder leads up to the sentry post above the gate,
while to the south is a road that leads down the hill into town.
~
